26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_bar_base.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "priv.h"
30
31void
32nvkm_bar_flush(struct nvkm_bar *bar)
33{
34 if (bar && bar->func->flush)
35 bar->func->flush(bar);
36}
37
38struct nvkm_vm *
39nvkm_bar_kmap(struct nvkm_bar *bar)
40{
41 /* disallow kmap() until after vm has been bootstrapped */
42 if (bar && bar->func->kmap && bar->subdev.oneinit)
43 return bar->func->kmap(bar);
44 return NULL;
45}
46
47int
48nvkm_bar_umap(struct nvkm_bar *bar, u64 size, int type, struct nvkm_vma *vma)
49{
50 return bar->func->umap(bar, size, type, vma);
51}
52
53static int
54nvkm_bar_oneinit(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
55{
56 struct nvkm_bar *bar = nvkm_bar(subdev);
57 return bar->func->oneinit(bar);
58}
59
60static int
61nvkm_bar_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
62{
63 struct nvkm_bar *bar = nvkm_bar(subdev);
64 return bar->func->init(bar);
65}
66
67static void *
68nvkm_bar_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
69{
70 struct nvkm_bar *bar = nvkm_bar(subdev);
71 return bar->func->dtor(bar);
72}
73
74static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
75nvkm_bar = {
76 .dtor = nvkm_bar_dtor,
77 .oneinit = nvkm_bar_oneinit,
78 .init = nvkm_bar_init,
79};
80
81void
82nvkm_bar_ctor(const struct nvkm_bar_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
83 int index, struct nvkm_bar *bar)
84{
85 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_bar, device, index, 0, &bar->subdev);
86 bar->func = func;
87 spin_lock_init(&bar->lock);
88}
